{{also|Polygon|polygón}}
==English==

===Etymology===
From {{der|en|grc|πολύγωνον}}, from {{m|grc|πολύς||many}} + {{m|grc|γωνία||angle}}, equivalent to {{af|en|poly-|-gon}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{IPA|en|/ˈpɒlɪɡən/|/ˈpɒliːˌɡɒn/|a=UK}}
* {{enPR|pälʹē-gän|a=US}}, {{IPA|en|/ˈpɑliˌɡɑn/}}
* {{audio|en|en-us-polygon.ogg|a=US}}
* {{hyphenation|en|pol|y|gon}}
* {{rhymes|en|ɒlɪɡən|ɒliːɡɒn|s=3}}

===Noun===
{{wp}}
{{en-noun}}
[[File:Assorted polygons.svg|thumb|300px|right|Polygons (sense 1)]]

# {{lb|en|geometry}} A [[plane]] [[figure]] bounded by [[edge]]s that are all [[straight line]]s.
# {{lb|en|geometry}} The [[boundary]] of such a figure.
# {{lb|en|geometry|more generally}} A figure comprising [[vertex|vertices]] and (not necessarily straight) edges, [[alternating]]ly.
# {{lb|en|geometry}} Such a figure and its [[interior]], taken as a whole.

